<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Lynx
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.ilhawaii.net/~stony/lore113.html
">Run, Rabbit, Run</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.sacred-texts.com/nam/ne/al/al45.htm
">Rabbit and the Lynx</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Mi'kmaq and Passamaquoddy stories about Lynx being outwitted by the trickster Rabbit.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.bigorrin.org/archive110.htm
">Innu Lynx Myth</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Innu story about a resourceful woman who tricks a greedy lynx into killing himself.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/Achaanwaapush-Cree.html
">The Cannibal Rabbit</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Cree legend about a group of lynx children who defeat a man-eating monster.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.calverley.ca/Part06-Legends/6-006.html
">The Magic Gifts</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Legend about a Cree hunter who won powerful Lynx medicine from a mysterious stranger.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.ourvoices.ca/index/ourvoices-story-action/id.0136
">Legend of the Giant Skunk</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Cree story about how Wolverine and Great Lynx defeated a giant skunk monster.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.ocbtracker.com/ladypixel/oldsqui.html
">Old Man and the Lynx</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/AMealforNataYowa-Blackfoot.html
">A Lynx Story</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Blackfoot legends explaining how lynx got their strange shape.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.civilization.ca/cmc/exhibitions/aborig/fp/fpz2f31e.shtml
">Mishebeshu</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ojibwe storytellers describe the legendary water lynx.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Lynx Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0807530476/natilangofthe-20
">Great Rabbit and the Long-Tailed Wildcat</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Children's book illustrating an Algonquin legend about how Wildcat lost his tail.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0226474720/natilangofthe-20
">The Story of Lynx</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Anthropological text on the meaning and importance of Coyote and Lynx myths in Native American tribes.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of American Indian tales about animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>



